      <akn:section eId="sec_14_302">
        <akn:num>14-302</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Testimony against deceased or incapable person.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_14-302_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>In a civil action against:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_14-302_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>In an action specified by subsection (a) of this section, if the plaintiff or his agent, servant, or employee, testifies as to any transaction with, or action, declaration, or admission of, the deceased or incapable person, an entry, memorandum, or declaration, oral or written, by the deceased or incapable person, made while he was capable and upon his personal knowledge, may not be excluded as hearsay.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
